/* Outline mode node chrome: paragraph indentation (by tree depth) and the
   paragraph leader marker. Scoped to paragraph lines only — list items,
   headings, and atoms already have their own native indentation/rendering,
   and a real-vault check found overriding it broke native hanging-indent
   math (checkbox/bullet layout went visibly wrong). Paragraphs have zero
   native indentation, so this is purely additive there.

   --to-indent-unit is a fixed rem value, not Obsidian's em-based
   --list-indent: em resolves against each line's OWN font size, and
   headings render at a larger font than paragraphs, so the same tree depth
   would otherwise draw a different pixel offset depending on which node
   happened to sit at that depth. rem is root-relative and stays fixed.

   The padding rule needs !important: Obsidian's own line styling sets
   padding via an equal-or-higher-specificity rule later in the cascade
   (verified: a plain class selector on .cm-line without !important was
   silently overridden, even on paragraph lines with no competing native
   padding of their own). */

:root {
	--to-indent-unit: 1.5rem;
}

.cm-editor .cm-line.to-node-line {
	position: relative;
	padding-left: calc(var(--to-depth, 0) * var(--to-indent-unit)) !important;
}

.cm-editor .cm-line.to-node-marker::after {
	content: '\2022'; /* • */
	position: absolute;
	top: 0;
	left: calc(var(--to-depth, 0) * var(--to-indent-unit) - 1.2rem);
	width: 1rem;
	text-align: center;
	color: var(--text-faint);
	background: transparent;
}

