/* Outline mode node chrome: one consistent indentation unit and marker
   style across every node kind (headings, paragraphs, list items, code/
   table/quote/callout/hr blocks).

   The mechanism: Obsidian already positions list bullets/checkboxes via a
   hanging-indent pair — text-indent: -Npx (pulls the first line's inline
   content, bullet included, left of the padding edge) + padding-left: Npx
   (where wrapped/continuation lines actually start), with N growing
   per raw list-nesting level. Overriding only one half of that pair (an
   earlier attempt) broke it outright. Here we own BOTH halves, uniformly,
   for every kind: padding-left: depth * --to-indent-unit, text-indent:
   -1 * --to-hang, applied together to every decorated line. That's the
   same mechanism Obsidian's own list bullets use, just driven by our tree
   depth instead of raw markdown nesting — so a `::before` marker glyph
   (for kinds with no native marker) hangs exactly the same way a native
   bullet does, no absolute-position math required. List items keep their
   own native bullet/number glyph and positioning; only its size/weight is
   restyled here, not its position.

   --to-indent-unit/--to-hang are fixed rem values, not Obsidian's em-based
   --list-indent: em resolves against each line's OWN font size, and
   headings render at a larger font than paragraphs, so the same tree depth
   would otherwise draw a different pixel offset depending on which kind
   happened to sit at that depth. rem is root-relative and stays fixed.

   padding-left/text-indent need !important: Obsidian's own line styling
   sets both via an equal-or-higher-specificity rule later in the cascade
   (verified: without !important the rule was silently overridden even on
   lines with no competing native value of their own). */

:root {
	--to-indent-unit: 1.5rem;
	--to-hang: 1.25rem;
}

.cm-editor .cm-line.to-node-line {
	padding-left: calc(var(--to-depth, 0) * var(--to-indent-unit)) !important;
}

.cm-editor .cm-line.to-node-first {
	text-indent: calc(-1 * var(--to-hang)) !important;
}

.cm-editor .cm-line.to-node-marker::before {
	content: '\25CF'; /* ● filled circle — a deliberately prominent, fat marker */
	display: inline-block;
	width: var(--to-hang);
	text-align: center;
	color: var(--text-muted);
	font-size: 0.6em;
	vertical-align: middle;
}

.cm-editor .cm-line.to-node-native-marker .list-bullet,
.cm-editor .cm-line.to-node-native-marker .list-number {
	font-weight: 700;
	font-size: 1.15em;
	color: var(--text-muted);
}

