   glyph and native position — only resized/bolded in place, not replaced
   or repositioned. A replace-with-a-round-dot attempt (via ::after +
   position:absolute) was tried and reverted: Obsidian's fold-indicator
   chevron (rendered for any list item that has children — a fixed-size
   element independent of our indentation scheme) collided with the
   repositioned dot, and manual pixel offsets to dodge it ended up
   overlapping the marker with the item's own text instead — worse than
   the original mismatch. Matching the native bullet's *shape* to our own
   marker is a cosmetic follow-up, not attempted further here; resizing
   in place is safe because it never moves anything, so it can't collide
   with fold indicators or text. */
.cm-editor .cm-line.to-node-native-marker .list-bullet,
.cm-editor .cm-line.to-node-native-marker .list-number {
	font-weight: 700;
	font-size: 1.15em;
	color: var(--text-muted);
